# Hummingbird k8s (control-plane) systemd preset.
#
# This file is deliberately identical to containers/k8s-worker/10-k8s-worker.preset
# in its bootc-update timer policy: both flavors disable the legacy
# bootc-fetch-apply-updates.timer (mutable :latest tracking) and enable the
# semver-aware bootc-semver-update.timer. See docs/auto-updates.md.
#
# The CP/worker auto-update posture split documented in docs/auto-updates.md
# (single-CP outage rationale, #48) is enforced at deploy-time by
# scripts/deploy-cluster.sh via the AUTO_UPDATE_CP cloud-init knob — NOT at
# the preset layer. The preset is uniform across flavors so a host promoted
# from worker to CP (or vice versa) keeps a consistent on-disk timer state;
# the cloud-init runcmd is the operator-controlled gate.
#
# If you came here thinking the two presets had "drifted" — they haven't.
# The drift is intentional and lives at the deploy-cluster layer. See #225.
disable bootc-fetch-apply-updates.timer
enable bootc-semver-update.timer
enable crio.service
enable kubelet.service
enable k8s-init.service
enable health-check-rollback.timer
